## Core Principles

### Understand Before Acting
- Never fix a symptom without understanding the root cause
- If you are unsure what a file does, read it before changing it
- If a bug report mentions one file, check 3-5 related files before writing any fix
- Describe the root cause before writing any code

### Plan Before Coding
- For any feature or fix: write a brief plan first, identify every file that will change
- Identify edge cases before coding — what happens if the user has no credits? What if the stream fails mid-way? What if the model returns an unexpected format?
- If a plan has more than 3 files changing, flag it and confirm before proceeding

### Test the Whole Path
- When fixing a bug, trace the entire request path: frontend → edge function → database → response
- Do not assume a fix is correct just because the isolated code looks right
- Always run `npm run build` after frontend changes to catch TypeScript errors

