## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- All new code must be TypeScript, not plain JavaScript
- No `any` types unless absolutely necessary — use proper interfaces
- Always handle the case where an API response field might be undefined
- Run `npm run build` after every change and fix all TypeScript errors before finishing

### Error Handling
- Every API call must have a try/catch
- Every edge function must return a proper error response with status code and message
- Never swallow errors silently (no empty catch blocks)
- User-facing errors must be human-readable, not raw error objects

### Edge Functions (Deno)
- Always verify JWT at the start: `supabase.auth.getUser(jwt)` 
- Return CORS headers on all responses
- Log errors with enough context to debug (`console.error('context:', error.message)`)
- Never return 200 for an error — use appropriate status codes (400, 401, 402, 500)

### Frontend State
- Use existing Zustand stores — do not create new global state management
- Do not add new `useState` hooks for data that belongs in an existing store
- Do not fetch data directly in components — use service files in `src/services/`

